FR940527-2-00179 FR940527-2-00137 [Dept. Circ. 570, 1993_Rev., Supp. No. 23] Surety Companies Acceptable on Federal Bonds, Termination of Authority: American Resources Insurance Company, Inc. Notice is hereby given that the Certificate of Authority issued by the Treasury to American Resources Insurance Company, Inc., of Mobile, Alabama, under the United States Code, Title 31, Sections 9304&hyph;9308, to qualify as an acceptable surety on Federal bonds is terminated effective March 11, 1994. The Company was last listed as an acceptable surety on Federal bonds at 58 FR 35784, July 1, 1993. With respect to any bonds currently in force with American Resources Insurance Company, Inc., bond-approving officers should secure new bonds with acceptable sureties in those instances where a significant amount of liability remains outstanding. In addition, bonds that are continuous in nature should not be renewed. Questions concerning this notice may be directed to the Department of the Treasury, Financial Management Service, Funds Management Division, Surety Bond Branch, Washington, DC 20227, telephone (202/FTS) 874&hyph;6765. Dated: March 11, 1994. Diane E. Clark, Assistant Commissioner, Financial Information, Financial Management Service. [FR Doc. 94&hyph;12916 Filed 5&hyph;26&hyph;94; 8:45 am] BILLING CODE 4810&hyph;35&hyph;M
